1)  Ok, during a raid always ask raid leaders permission before summoning a pet, they can cause agro, break mez (which chanters just LOVE lol), and if your moving they can get left behind since they aren't very fast and then cause a train.  If the raid leader does give pet summoning permission then you should have a hot key to destroy it in a moments notice!  Don't trust yourself to type fast enough make a hotkey!  In Plains like Hate, you will not want to use a pet unless the tanks begin to fall.  If you have only 4 or 5 tanks left and they aren't looking too good on hp summon some pets and send them in to take the heat off the remaining tanks and give them a chance to take a break.  Normally during raids on places like Kael you will use Fire pets and water pets since fire pets have wizzy spells and Water pets will backstab.  Don't use EARTH pets on raids that root can cause a LOT of trouble.  Air I don't suggest very much since the lower hp and even though they ahve high Agi they still will be being hit for 100-200 dmg or something.  So they wont last very long.<br>
<br>
<br>
2)  With groups the mage pet is a bit more prominent, he can tank, take agro, and even be a wizard in the group.  Now, in certain situations such as if the cleric or chanter is in deep trouble and things look grim and you need to break your pet off from the main tank and send it on the mob attacking the chanter or cleric.  That way he can get away, heal or mez and your group is saved.<br>
Also, when grouping, dont bother buffing your pet, he is expendable, that 54 warrior over there isn't, so buff the people before the pets.  also, if things are looking bad and your going to need to run tell the group to begin backing off and then send pet in to hold the mobs off while you run for the zone.  Pets casn be very useful if you know how to use them.  Also you might want to think about pertnering with a necro to fear kite.  Would probably make a good team.<br>
<br>
3) ok, your soloing and you have your pet out.  Now, you'll want to use either an Air (cuase of high Agi and less chance of being hit not to mention stun) or Water for backstab and second most hp.  Some of you may be asking &quot;Why backstab with a water pet?&quot;  Well, you do this you use bolt spells to get agro, and kite the mob some with the water pet Backstabing, now, this is not a procedure I suggest unless you have a necro or druid or ranger with snare.  but it IS possible to do.  normally use Air since they have high agi and third most hp, and heal the pet once it is at 50% health, only cast once on the mob at the end and make sure the pet is BUFFED and has DS on!  It really makes a BIG difference.  Having your pet quad for 50 and then the other mob hits him for 12 44 and 34, that mob just took 75dmg from the dmg shield!  It makes a big difference.  Don't waist anything.  Use everything you have at your disposal, use Malosi spells to pull.  The spell will debuff making pet spells more affectitive and the agro on it is so low pet taunts once and never has to do it again to get agro off you.  Also will make your spells likly to do max dmg.<br>
<br>
Hop[e this helps some and if anyone has some info on Pets please post it =)<br>
